# Elementor widgets: icons & SVG color behavior

When converting static sections to Elementor widgets, **avoid uploading colored images for icons** when the design expects hover color changes.

- **Preferred**: Use Elementor **Icon control** (`Controls_Manager::ICONS`) per item (e.g., inside a Repeater).
- **Render**: Use `Elementor\Icons_Manager::render_icon()` so the icon uses `currentColor`.
- **Styling**: Wrap the rendered icon in an element that carries Tailwind-like color classes:
  - Normal: `text-primary`
  - Hover: `group-hover:text-white`
  - Keep your existing container hover (e.g., `group-hover:bg-primary`) so icon + background swap together.

## Example pattern

```php
use Elementor\Controls_Manager;
use Elementor\Icons_Manager;

$repeater->add_control(
  'icon',
  [
    'label' => __('Card Icon', 'bina'),
    'type' => Controls_Manager::ICONS,
  ]
);

// render
if (!empty($item['icon']['value'])) {
  echo '<span class="text-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors">';
  Icons_Manager::render_icon($item['icon'], ['aria-hidden' => 'true']);
  echo '</span>';
}
```

## Avoid

- Uploading **PNG/JPG/WebP** icons if you need color transitions (CSS can’t recolor them reliably).
- Inline SVGs with hardcoded `fill="#..."` / `stroke="#..."` when hover should recolor.
